Let me put it in code terms. In the following template script:<p><pre><code>    <div>@hello</div>
</code></pre>
The generated code can be like (not including runtime lib):<p><pre><code>    var ___html = &quot;&quot;;
    var hello = hasown.call(data, &quot;hello&quot;) ? data.hello : &quot;&quot;;

    ___html += &#x27;<div>&#x27; +
                safeString(hello, HTML_GENERIC) +
                &#x27;</div>&#x27;;

    return ___html;
</code></pre>
Which gives same effect as `with`.
